'''Ali Ahmed''' (born October 10, 2000) is a Canadian professional [[association football|soccer <!--Ahmed is Canadian, do not change to football-->]] player who plays as a [[wide midfielder]] or [[winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|NorwichC}} club [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] and the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada national team]].

==Early life==
Ahmed was born in Toronto to parents from [[Ethiopia]].<ref name=road/> He began playing youth soccer at age six with the [[North Toronto Nitros]].<ref>{{Canada Soccer player|56537}}</ref> In 2018, he went on trial with the [[Toronto FC Academy]], who were ready to sign him to join the academy, but he opted to head to Portugal to trial with the U19 side of [[C.F. Os Belenenses]], but was unable to sign as he was under 18.<ref name=road>{{Cite web|url=https://theprovince.com/sports/soccer/mls/vancouver-whitecaps/the-road-less-travelled-for-whitecaps-prospect-ali-ahmed|title=The road less travelled for Whitecaps prospect Ali Ahmed|date=April 27, 2022|first=J.J.|last=Adams|work=[[The Province]]}}</ref> He then went to Spain, before returning to Toronto, before returning to Europe to trial in Portugal, the United Kingdom, and the Netherlands.<ref name=road /> In November 2019, he trialed with the [[Vancouver Whitecaps Academy]] and then trialed again the following year,<ref name=road /> and in August 2020, he joined the [[Vancouver Whitecaps Academy]].<ref name=know>{{cite web|url=https://aftn.ca/whitecaps-fc-2-are-back-get-to-know-the-new-squad-part-two/|date=March 19, 2022|title=Whitecaps FC 2 are back – Get to know the new squad (Part Two)|first=Michael|last=McColl|work=Away from the Numbers}}</ref> In 2021, he played with the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC U-23]].<ref name=know /> He attended pre-season camp with the first team in 2021 and 2022.<ref name=know />

==Club career==

=== Whitecaps FC 2 ===
In March 2022, he signed a professional contract with [[Whitecaps FC 2]] in [[MLS Next Pro]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/wfc2/news/wfc2-sign-two-canadians-and-four-2022-mls-superdraft-picks|title=WFC2 sign two Canadians and four 2022 MLS SuperDraft picks|date=March 18, 2022|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> He made his professional debut on March 26 against [[Houston Dynamo 2]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/wfc2/news/wfc2-open-inaugural-mls-next-pro-season-with-narrow-1-0-loss-against-houston-dyn|first=Maxim|last=Fossey|date=March 26, 2022|title=WFC2 open inaugural MLS NEXT Pro season with narrow 1-0 loss against Houston Dynamo 2|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> He led the team in assists with five in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.area51sportsnet.com/2022/10/19/terminal-city-thoughts-a-look-at-a-few-whitecaps-2-players/|title=Terminal City Thoughts: A look at a few Whitecaps 2 players|date=October 19, 2022|first=Nathan|last=Durec|work=Area 51 Sports Network}}</ref> He was named the 2022 WFC2 Player of the Year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/whitecaps-fc-announce-winners-for-2022-player-awards|title=Whitecaps FC announce winners for 2022 Player Awards|date=October 28, 2022|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref>

=== Vancouver Whitecaps FC ===
On April 22, 2022, he joined the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC|first team]] on a short-term four-day loan ahead of their [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] league match against [[Austin FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/whitecaps-fc-sign-wfc2-wingback-ali-ahmed-and-midfielder-vasco-fry-to-mls-short-|title=Whitecaps FC sign WFC2 wingback Ali Ahmed and midfielder Vasco Fry to MLS short-term agreements|date=April 22, 2022|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> In the match the next day, he made his official first-team debut.<ref>{{cite tweet|author=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]|user=WhitecapsFC|number=1518065035335012352|title=Ali Ahmed's MLS Debut @aliahmed51_ #VWFC #ATXvVAN|access-date=November 1, 2022}}</ref> On August 4, he signed another short-term loan with Vancouver.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/whitecaps-fc-sign-wingback-ali-ahmed-and-striker-simon-becher-to-mls-short-term-|title=Whitecaps FC sign wingback Ali Ahmed and striker Simon Becher to MLS short-term agreements|date=August 4, 2022|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> In November 2022, he signed a permanent contract with the first team for the 2023 season, becoming the first Whitecaps FC 2 player to sign a first-team contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/whitecaps-fc-sign-mls-next-pro-wingback-ali-ahmed-to-an-mls-contract-through-202|title=Whitecaps FC sign MLS NEXT Pro wingback Ali Ahmed to an MLS contract through 2025|date=November 16, 2022|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> On May 24, he suffered what appeared to be a serious injury in a match, where he lost consciousness and was treated on-field for seventeen minutes,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadiansoccerdaily.com/2023/05/26/ali-ahmed-posts-thank-you-message-insists-hell-be-back-on-the-pitch-with-vancouver-whitecaps-soon/|title=Ali Ahmed posts thank you message, insists he'll be back on the pitch with Vancouver Whitecaps soon|date=May 26, 2023|work=Canadian Soccer Daily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://thethirdsub.ca/2023/05/25/horror-ali-ahmed-injury-overshadows-whitecaps-canadian-championship-win/|title=Scary Ali Ahmed injury overshadows Whitecaps' Canadian Championship win|work=The Third Sub|first=Andrew|last=Bahl|date=May 25, 2023}}</ref> but was released from hospital the next day with only a concussion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://northerntribune.ca/whitecaps-ali-ahmed-injury/|title=Ali Ahmed Cleared By Hospital, Returns To Team|date=May 25, 2023|work=Northern Tribune|first=John|last=Jacques}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/mls/article/whitecaps-ali-ahmed-taken-to-hospital-after-scary-tackle-in-canadian-championship/|title=Whitecaps' Ali Ahmed cleared to travel with team after leaving hospital|date=May 24, 2023|work=[[Sportsnet]]}}</ref> On June 7, 2023, he won the [[2023 Canadian Championship]] with the Whitecaps, defeating [[CF Montreal]] and won the tournament's Best Young Canadian Player Award.<ref name=young>{{Cite web|url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/gressel-and-ahmed-win-awards-at-2023-canadian-championship/|title=Gressel and Ahmed win awards at 2023 Canadian Championship|date=June 8, 2023|work=[[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref>

=== Norwich City ===
On January 4, 2026, Ahmed moved to England, signing for [[EFL Championship]] side [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] on a three-and-a-half-year deal with an option for a further year.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 January 2026 |title=Norwich City complete signing of Ali Ahmed |url=https://canaries.co.uk/content/norwich-city-complete-signing-of-ali-ahmed |access-date=5 January 2026 |website=Norwich City |language=en}}</ref>

He made his debut for the club on 17 January 2026, starting the match and providing an assist within the opening 10 minutes against [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Que |first=Brandon |date=2026-01-17 |title=WATCH: Ali Ahmed assists Norwich opener in English Championship debut against Wrexham |url=https://canadiansoccerdaily.com/2026/01/17/watch-ali-ahmed-assists-norwich-opener-in-english-championship-debut-against-wrexham/ |access-date=2026-01-18 |website=Canadian Soccer Daily |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-01-17 |title=STARTING XIs: Ahmed City debut against Wrexham; Slimane start |url=https://www.pinkun.com/sport/matchpreviews/25773606.wrexham-v-norwich-city-team-news-starting-line-ups/ |access-date=2026-01-18 |website=The Pink Un |language=en}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Norwich three days later in a 5–0 victory over [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Norwich thrash West Brom to move out of drop zone |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c7v0l0yd87et |access-date=2026-01-26 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 26 January 2026, he recorded a goal and an assist in a 2–1 victory against league leaders [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Norwich City Football Club |url=https://www.canaries.co.uk/ |access-date=2026-01-26 |website=Norwich City Football Club |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
In May 2023, Ahmed was listed on the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]] preliminary roster for the [[2023 CONCACAF Nations League Finals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadiansoccerdaily.com/2023/05/19/concacaf-drops-stacked-canada-preliminary-nations-league-roster-with-some-surprise-names/|date=May 19, 2023|title=CONCACAF drops stacked Canada preliminary Nations League roster with some surprise names|access-date=May 19, 2023|work=Canada Soccer Daily}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprovince.com/sports/soccer/mls/vancouver-whitecaps/whitecaps-leading-against-pacific-but-all-thoughts-are-with-ali-ahmed-after-horrific-injury|title=Scary injury to Ali Ahmed casts pall over Vancouver Whitecaps victory|date=May 24, 2023|first=J.J.|last=Adams|work=[[The Province]]}}</ref> In June 2023, he was named to the final 23-man squad for the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/ahmed-called-up-canada-gold-cup|date=June 19, 2023|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]|title=Ali Ahmed called up to Canada MNT for Concacaf Gold Cup}}</ref> Ahmed made his debut for Canada on June 27 in their tournament opener against [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/mls-rookies-amhed-bombito-inspire-in-canada-s-gold-cup-opener|title=MLS rookies Amhed, Bombito inspire in Canada's Gold Cup opener|work=[[Major League Soccer]]|first=Ben|last=Steiner|date=June 28, 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadiansoccerdaily.com/2023/06/28/fearless-ali-ahmeds-canada-debut-marks-latest-high-point-for-breakout-vancouver-whitecaps-star/|title='Fearless' Ali Ahmed's Canada debut marks latest high point for breakout Vancouver Whitecaps star|first=Tom|last=Nightingale|date=June 28, 2023|work=Canadian Soccer Daily}}</ref>

In June 2024, Ahmed was named to Canada's squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://canadasoccer.com/news/canmnt-announce-2024-copa-america-roster/|title=CANMNT ANNOUNCE 2024 COPA AMÉRICA ROSTER|date=June 15, 2024|work= [[Canadian Soccer Association]]}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Ahmed is a [[Muslim]] and fasts during the month of [[Ramadan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprovince.com/sports/soccer/mls/vancouver-whitecaps/ramadan-a-mental-test-for-pro-athletes |title=Ramadan a 'shower for the soul' but a mental test for pro athletes |website=theprovince.com |date=2024-03-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/aahmed22_/p/C4Y8FvYPMYI/?img_index=1 |title=Ramadan Mubarak to all my brothers and sisters! |website=Instagram}}</ref>

